-- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi has accused Amnesty International of applying double standard in the assessment of human rights violation in the country. He was speaking at both the Kenyan International Conference Center and the Kenya Science Teachers College during a workshop of the stakeholders in the small-scale enterprises. The president wondered why government officers serving in the police force were never regarded as victims of human rights violation whenever they were murdered or injured during their course of duty. The Kenyan Head of State pointed out that Amnesty International treated police officers as if they were not part
